            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1698169354491-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1698169354491-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1698169354491-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1698169354491-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>peri peri sauce</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a separate large bowl with your <strong>diced</strong> <strong>chicken breast</strong> and mix well until they're fully coated</p><p>Chop your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> roughly</p><p>Tip: Slice into rings for speedy chopping</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1698169361195-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1698169361195-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1698169361195-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1698169361195-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1698169361195-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to a<strong> tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 5-10 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once the pepper has had an initial 5-10 min, add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>chicken breast </strong>to the tray[s] and return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>peri peri chicken breast</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1698169367185-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1698169367185-x400.jpg",
