            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is done, transfer to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Add the <strong>cooked chicken </strong>and <strong>cooked pepper</strong> with the <strong>drained farfalle</strong> to the <strong>peri peri pasta sauce</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce begins to stick to the<strong> </strong>pasta</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the starchy pasta water if it's looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
